<br>
Here is the test I think is very important to do:<br>
<br>
Use your two-handed sword and do your PA, then hit the same level of mob without a PA or any style and record the damage. (i prefer level -0- greys, or you could do a large test with a parser and tons of mobs to get averages). The second number you get we will call base damage. <br>
<br>
Total - Base = PA damage.<br>
<br>
Your base with a 2-h sword should be much higher.<br>
<br>
Then do the test again but use a 1-h sword, a quick one if you can get it.<br>
<br>
Total - Base = PA damage<br>
<br>
My theory is that you will get the same number for PA damage in both cases. <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFF
